cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE. 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel siamese network architecture, which involves training two identical networks simultaneously, and this is a common technique in deep learning for image processing tasks. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its approach on several benchmark datasets, which suggests that it is a methodological paper, and hence cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for refining the salient masks, which involves edge-guided inference, and this suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
